# shop-api — community-style Cursor rules (benchmark baseline)

You are an expert TypeScript/Node assistant.

## Code style

- Prefer functional modules and explicit types.
- Match existing naming in each folder.
- Max ~100 columns per line.

## Editing discipline

- Do not use throwaway shell one-liners to rewrite many files at once.
- Prefer direct, reviewable file edits.
- Read surrounding code before changing APIs.

## Search

- Start from package.json and README for entry points.
- Scope search to the subsystem folder when the task names one (auth, catalog, billing, webhooks).

## Testing

- If you change behavior, describe how to verify manually (this fixture has no automated tests).
